{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fb17970-f4c4-437f-a3fd-9b3f272f023b","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a real `ContentPage` property in .NET MAUI — that's why it has no effect. You need two things:\n\n**1. iOS — disable safe-area insets:**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"\n             Padding=\"0\">\n```\n\n**2. Android — transparent system bars** (in `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`):\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    Window!.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n    Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n}\n```\n\n**3. Image — fill the space:**\n```xml\n<Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n       Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n       VerticalOptions=\"Fill\"\n       HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n```\n\nThe key takeaway: on iOS it's `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"`, and on Android you must make the system bars transparent so content draws behind them. Also ensure `Padding=\"0\"` on the page (MAUI can inject safe-area padding by default on iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e653caa1-7ea0-4622-ae9a-92b4388582ee","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making an image go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, going behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still have padding.\n\nThis is a .NET MAUI question about ignoring safe areas for full-screen/edge-to-edge content. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, `SafeAreaEdges` is not a property on `ContentPage`. The correct approach depends on the platform:\n\nFor .NET MAUI, to achieve edge-to-edge display:\n\n\n- On iOS, I need to use platform-specific markup to disable the safe area\n- On Android, the approach involves handling system bars and window insets differently\n- The standard MAUI property the user mentioned doesn't actually exist on ContentPage, so I should clarify the correct way to handle this across both platforms The issue is that `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` isn't a valid MAUI property. For iOS, I need to use the platform-specific `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` configuration, and for Android with .NET 10, edge-to-edge rendering is enforced by default but requires handling window insets and setting the status/navigation bars to transparent. I should also make sure `Padding=\"0\"` is set on the ContentPage itself.","outputTokens":1229,"requestId":"143B:19082:309F32:379611:6A03CF3C"},"id":"6708409a-2f71-4b96-b220-2a92168e5180","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:09:41.040Z","parentId":"e35c35b4-2ad2-4730-9959-b35947e178d4"}
